Author: Gateway#3763
Content:
[telegram] <Regnar> Yes it does! The AtomicAPI is the backend engine that let's anyone build a DEX using the API and immediately get access to a single shared liquidity pool. This means HyperDEX desktop app shares liquidity with Chainswap desktop app, which shares liquidity with AtomicDEX mobile app, and anyone else, even if they are JUST running the engine on their computer. 
So these DEXs all have their different fee structures built into their GUI (The API gives fee ability to be easily implemented for GUI developers) to make revenues as people use their GUI, but still share liquidity with other GUIs.
See developer docs here:
https://developers.atomicdex.io/basic-docs/atomicdex/introduction-to-atomicdex.html (re @Suzycrabgrass: What are the benefits of using an atomic dex pool. We need network effects. I should be able to open my own atomicdex and get fees. This way people can do icos and get more people interested into the atomicdex babies.)
